abstract: Hong Kong football fans booed as the Chinese national anthem was played on Wednesday before their team's clash with China in South Korea as the political turmoil that has gripped the former British colony spilled over to the sports world.
snippet: Hong Kong football fans booed as the Chinese national anthem was played on Wednesday before their team's clash with China in South Korea as the political turmoil that has gripped the former British colony spilled over to the sports world.
lead_paragraph: BUSAN, South Korea — Hong Kong football fans booed as the Chinese national anthem was played on Wednesday before their team's clash with China in South Korea as the political turmoil that has gripped the former British colony spilled over to the sports world.
headline_main: Hong Kong Fans Boo National Anthem Ahead of Soccer Match With China
headline_print_headline: Hong Kong Fans Boo National Anthem Ahead of Soccer Match With China

abstract: Former British prime minister Tony Blair, Labour's most successful leader, on Wednesday urged the party to rebuild from electoral humiliation by rejecting the "protest movement with cult trimmings" created by outgoing leader Jeremy Corbyn.
snippet: Former British prime minister Tony Blair, Labour's most successful leader, on Wednesday urged the party to rebuild from electoral humiliation by rejecting the "protest movement with cult trimmings" created by outgoing leader Jeremy Corbyn.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Former British prime minister Tony Blair, Labour's most successful leader, on Wednesday urged the party to rebuild from electoral humiliation by rejecting the "protest movement with cult trimmings" created by outgoing leader Jeremy Corbyn.
headline_main: Ex-PM Blair Tells Britain's Labour: Change or You Will Disappear
headline_print_headline: Ex-PM Blair Tells Britain's Labour: Change or You Will Disappear

abstract: The Trump administration is finalizing a set of narrow rules to limit exports of sophisticated technology to adversaries like China, a document seen by Reuters shows, in a boon to U.S. industry that feared a much tougher crackdown on sales abroad.
snippet: The Trump administration is finalizing a set of narrow rules to limit exports of sophisticated technology to adversaries like China, a document seen by Reuters shows, in a boon to U.S. industry that feared a much tougher crackdown on sales abroad.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Trump administration is finalizing a set of narrow rules to limit exports of sophisticated technology to adversaries like China, a document seen by Reuters shows, in a boon to U.S. industry that feared a much tougher crackdown on sales abroad.
headline_main: U.S. Finalizing Rules to Limit Sensitive Tech Exports to China, Others
headline_print_headline: U.S. Finalizing Rules to Limit Sensitive Tech Exports to China, Others

abstract: Resistance is futile. Rey, Finn and Poe are back; so is Kylo Ren. No spoilers here.
snippet: Resistance is futile. Rey, Finn and Poe are back; so is Kylo Ren. No spoilers here.
lead_paragraph: Not that anybody has asked, but if I had to come up with a definitive ranking of all the “Star Wars” episodes — leaving out sidebars like the animated “Clone Wars,” the young Han Solo movie and the latest “Mandalorian” Baby Yoda memes — the result could only be a nine-way tie for fourth place.

abstract: The former Portuguese colony, now a global gambling hub, has been more willing than its neighbor to accept Beijing’s authority.
snippet: The former Portuguese colony, now a global gambling hub, has been more willing than its neighbor to accept Beijing’s authority.
lead_paragraph: MACAU — When Macau, the Portuguese colony turned Chinese gambling hub, got a new chief executive in October, the vote by an electoral committee was unanimous. He ran unopposed. No one took to the streets in protest.

abstract: Communicastions and health care stocks are leading major US indexes slightly higher in early trading on Wall Street. Facebook rose 1.6% and Eli Lilly added 3.1%. FedEx plunged after reporting a 40% earnings drop in its most recent quarter. The shipping giant is also suffering as its relationship soured with Amazon. The S&P 500 index rose 4 points, or 0.1%, to 3,196. The Dow Jones Industrial Average added 26 points, or 0.1%, to 28,292. The Nasdaq rose 16 points, or 0.2%, to 8,840. Bond prices didn't move much. The yield on the 10-year Treasury held steady at 1.89%.

lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — Communicastions and health care stocks are leading major US indexes slightly higher in early trading on Wall Street. Facebook rose 1.6% and Eli Lilly added 3.1%. FedEx plunged after reporting a 40% earnings drop in its most recent quarter. The shipping giant is also suffering as its relationship soured with Amazon. The S&P 500 index rose 4 points, or 0.1%, to 3,196. The Dow Jones Industrial Average added 26 points, or 0.1%, to 28,292. The Nasdaq rose 16 points, or 0.2%, to 8,840. Bond prices didn't move much. The yield on the 10-year Treasury held steady at 1.89%.
headline_main: Stock Indexes Open Slightly Higher, Led by Communications

abstract: The formal accord, after a preliminary deal in October, still requires months of work to integrate the automakers.
snippet: The formal accord, after a preliminary deal in October, still requires months of work to integrate the automakers.
lead_paragraph: Fiat Chrysler and PSA of France said Wednesday that they had agreed to the terms of a merger that would create the world’s fourth largest automaker.

abstract: China's President Xi Jinping arrived in Macau on Wednesday to celebrate the 20th anniversary of its handover to China, and is expected to announce economic perks as a reward for its stability and loyalty as protests rock nearby Hong Kong.
snippet: China's President Xi Jinping arrived in Macau on Wednesday to celebrate the 20th anniversary of its handover to China, and is expected to announce economic perks as a reward for its stability and loyalty as protests rock nearby Hong Kong.
lead_paragraph: MACAU/HONG KONG — China's President Xi Jinping arrived in Macau on Wednesday to celebrate the 20th anniversary of its handover to China, and is expected to announce economic perks as a reward for its stability and loyalty as protests rock nearby Hong Kong.
headline_main: Chinese Leader Xi Visits Gambling Hub Macau as Nearby Hong Kong Seethes
headline_print_headline: Chinese Leader Xi Visits Gambling Hub Macau as Nearby Hong Kong Seethes

abstract: Kazakh President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev on Wednesday named Nurlan Nogayev, previously a provincial governor, as energy minister - a key position in the oil- and gas-exporting nation - and reshuffled a number of other senior officials.
snippet: Kazakh President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev on Wednesday named Nurlan Nogayev, previously a provincial governor, as energy minister - a key position in the oil- and gas-exporting nation - and reshuffled a number of other senior officials.
lead_paragraph: ALMATY — Kazakh President Kassym-Jomart Tokayev on Wednesday named Nurlan Nogayev, previously a provincial governor, as energy minister - a key position in the oil- and gas-exporting nation - and reshuffled a number of other senior officials.
headline_main: Kazakh President Names New Energy Minister in High-Level Reshuffle
headline_print_headline: Kazakh President Names New Energy Minister in High-Level Reshuffle
